  "doc_id": "47411",
  "text": "PCR amplifications were performed with an MX3000P (Strategene, LA Jolla, CA, USA) instrument, as previously described by [CITATION_1] . The reaction mixture (25 µl) contained Platinum SYBR Green qPCR Super Mix UDG (11733; Invitrogene, Carlsbad, CA, USA), 0.2 µM of each primer and 5 µl of genomic DNA diluted -10 fold. The following primers were used LactoR`F (5`-CACAATGGACG(A/C)AAGTCTGATG-3`) and LBFR (5`-CGCCACTGGTGTTCTTCCAT-3`) [CITATION_2] . The amplification program was 50˚C for 2 min and 95˚C for 2 min, 35 cycles of 95˚C for 30 s, 60˚C for 15 s, 72˚C for 20 s, and then 95˚C for 1 min and 55˚ for 30 s.",
